{
  "texts": [
    "Results from SAC are compared with TQC, and we showed the improvement by TQC, which attenuates overestimation in neural networks.It was shown that model-free RL was able to discover a nearly optimal control strategy without any prior knowledge of the system dynamics using partial realistic measurements, exploiting only input-output data from the simulation environment.",
    "Therefore, this particular study on RL-based active flow control in 2-D laminar flow simulations can be seen as a step towards controlling the complex dynamics of three-dimensional turbulent flows in practical applications by replacing the simulation environment with the experimental set-up.",
    "Also, the frame stack method employed here to convert the POMDP to an MDP can be replaced by recurrent neural networks and attention-based architectures, which may further improve control performance in a scenario with complex dynamics.",
